Privacy Policy for Hydrant Flow Test Application

Effective Date: 2/24/2025

Thank you for using the Hydrant Flow Test Application ("the App"). Your privacy is very important to us. This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding any information you provide while using the App.

Information Collection and Use
No Data Collection:
The App is designed solely as a quick reference tool for calculating hydrant flow and available fire flow (AFF) based on the data you manually enter. We do not collect, store, or share any personal data or any other information from users. All calculations are performed locally on your device, and no data is transmitted to any external servers.

Data Security
Local Data Handling:
Since no data is collected or stored on external servers, there is no risk of your information being compromised. All data remains on your device and is completely under your control.

Third-Party Services
No Third-Party Integrations:
The App does not integrate with any third-party services that collect or process user data.

Children's Privacy
Not Intended for Children:
The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any information from children under 13.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
Policy Updates:
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
bdara@outlook.com

By using the App, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.
